actually my motivations are SO selfish because every new thing I learn brings me one step closer to understanding Phil better and I crave the feeling that gives me. I love learning so much.
I think regardless of whether I’ll pick up anything worth publishing if and when I go to Tulsa on my own dime, I’m still bringing something new and fresh to the table.

I want to pick up the pace. I think I’m ready to. a good chunk of this year was eaten up by my waiting on the WGC, which I’m not sure was the right call. but my logic was that if there was anything important I could bring to the show by researching there it was worth the wait

I’ve never felt this good about any other creative endeavor of mine, I’ve never been consistent before. I think it helps to know that my work is important. and even if it doesn’t reach a million people, it’ll be available for the people who are curious about Phil.
I went back and listened to my first two episodes, and with a good amount of distance between then and now I can happily say I’m proud of what I’ve produced so far.

I have to put my all into this project but if I don’t work at a comfortable pace I fear that I’ll get burnt out and abandon it. I think I got over the hump though, I’ve been at it for over a year and haven’t quit yet. which is why everyone’s support means so much to me.
I really appreciate everyone being patient with me and I hope the Legacy episodes have helped tide you over.
